OL,6,FJanet Brownlow, representing James,
OL,7,Fsaid her client had attended the
OL,8,Fprotest "out of curiosity" and wanted
OL,9,Fto stress that he is "not a racist".
OL,11,FShe said James had picked up the
OL,12,Fknuckle duster at a property he had
OL,13,Fpreviously worked on, and left it in
OL,14,Fhis van, from where he had picked it
OL,15,Fup and then put it on before the
OL,16,Fprotest.
OL,18,F"He put it on his fingers and couldn't
OL,19,Fget it off," Ms Brownlow told the
OL,20,Fcourt.
